			<td><br>David Hanson is widely regarded amongst the world robotics industry as both a leader and a visionary. His core innovations come from years of research on building robots and their accompanying materials, such as Frubber™, mechanics (including servo-motors and battery-powering capability) and software (AI itself, or the "brain" and "vocabulary" of each robot). David founded Hanson Robotics in late 2003 to commercialize social robot characters and their constituent technologies.  He received his Ph.D. from the University of Texas at Dallas in Humanities with a major in Aesthetic Studies and holds a BFA from the Rhode Island School of Design.</td>
